<br>
For a long time, Jenquai Explorers were the most popular class due to cloaking and wormholes, but after the last few patches, wormholing for trade runs and quick cash is no longer viable, and JE's have a much harder time with combat, so their popularity has declined somewhat, although they are still popular.  <br>
<br>
Terrrans are a mixed bag.  All of the hard-core builders are Terran Traders of course, and they are popular due to their ability to fight pretty darn well.  Terran warriors are also popular because of their great stand-off attacks with missles, which are expensive, but are sickingly powerful now.<br>
<br>
Progen Warriors are always popular because of the status as the 'tank' of E&amp;B.  Projectiles have been buffed, and now that warp speeds are cut across the board, their slow speed isn't such a big problem anymore.  End-game PW's are still godlike, and therefore are probably as popular as JE's.<br>
<br>
Then theres my class, PE's.  They aren't as good at stealth as JE's by any means, but they benefit from Progen shields and projectiles, and are exceptionally good fighters.  They are as close to a hybrid as you can get, but to a clever player, they are definately the most flexable, most self-reliant class in the game.  They didn't use to be popular at all, but more and more people are starting to play them.  They are still pretty low on the played class pole though.<br>
<br>
Finally, people still love Defenders.  The aren't as powerful as Progen of Terran warriors, but their PSI shields rock, especially after the across-the-board shield strength reduction.  There's something to be said for a hefty one-shot shield, and because of that, they are pretty popular, plus, you don't have to fret over ammo costs as much since you'll normally be using beam weapons.  <br>
<br>
So, my best guess, most popular to least:<br>
<br>
JE<br>
JD<br>
PW<br>
TW<br>
TT<br>
PE <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prybutok>Prybutok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 842<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/15/02 10:52:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3251.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://prybutok.homestead.com/files/djprymini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I have a lvl 15 JE I started yesterday. I've gotten to the point right now that I can't complete my quests because they send me to areas that garner me only XP debt. So I'm sitting around in the newbie area slowly getting my combat skills up and wondering if maybe I want to make another character.<br>
